29
00:01:47,551 --> 00:01:48,312
[SPEAKER_06]: So good evening.

30
00:01:48,912 --> 00:01:53,816
[SPEAKER_06]: We're here to present our fiscal year 27 preliminary operating budget.

31
00:01:54,356 --> 00:02:04,764
[SPEAKER_06]: This presentation is responsible, thoughtful, and authentic representation of the work we have undertaken to support the growth and development of every student in Medford Public Schools.

32
00:02:05,724 --> 00:02:09,287
[SPEAKER_06]: This budget cycle follows a year of significant progress.

33
00:02:09,547 --> 00:02:13,190
[SPEAKER_06]: We continue to successfully operationalize our instructional vision.

34
00:02:14,356 --> 00:02:23,143
[SPEAKER_06]: through new consolidated schedules district-wide at the elementary, middle, and high school levels, first time seen at the high school level.

35
00:02:23,884 --> 00:02:29,749
[SPEAKER_06]: We've also implemented in the district 15 minutes of instructional time across the district, K through 12 plus.

36
00:02:30,549 --> 00:02:37,235
[SPEAKER_06]: These changes alongside our commitment to our collective bargaining agreements are deeply rooted in our core value of belonging.

37
00:02:38,386 --> 00:02:43,568
[SPEAKER_06]: However, we also must address and you will see this evening the realities of the current economic landscape.

38
00:02:44,089 --> 00:02:56,895
[SPEAKER_06]: And like many districts across the Commonwealth, we are navigating an unavoidable rising costs in special education, transportation, and general operations to meet these challenges.

39
00:02:57,690 --> 00:03:10,420
[SPEAKER_06]: Our leadership team has worked and continues to work alongside school and department leaders to ensure that we have intentional alignment with the evolving needs of our students, our staff and our community.

40
00:03:11,541 --> 00:03:22,229
[SPEAKER_06]: This preliminary proposal this evening is the result of months of critical discussion, public feedback and a collaborative problem solving stance from our entire administrative team.

41
00:03:23,185 --> 00:03:33,015
[SPEAKER_06]: I want to thank Jerry McHugh, our budget analyst, our finance director, Noel Velez, for their continued and long efforts.

42
00:03:33,775 --> 00:03:45,327
[SPEAKER_06]: This work is iterative, and it serves as a testament to our values of consistency and coherence that we are working quite hard to establish as through lines across every level of the district.

43
00:03:46,527 --> 00:03:53,153
[SPEAKER_06]: We're moving toward a unified vision that ensures all resources support our shared educational and operational goals.

44
00:03:54,554 --> 00:04:03,481
[SPEAKER_06]: And with that, I'm going to turn it over to Mr. McHugh and Mr. Velez to present the preliminary proposal.

45
